{"ts":"2026-06-26T08:32:05.693Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"j37iyou7","input":{"summary":"I have successfully completed the accessibility and motion quality pass across the entire GFF AI platform. All public pages are now exceptionally accessible, keyboard-navigable, semantic, and optimized for screen readers, while perfectly maintaining the premium, editorial 2026 Figma aesthetic of GFF AI.\n\n### Summary of Changes & Achievements:\n1. **Semantic Headings (`<h1>` check):** Verified that every public page contains exactly one `<h1>` header, located in either the shared `InnerPageHero` component or the main landing page `HeroSection`.\n2. **Accessible Custom SVG Interactive Diagrams:** Formally transformed SVG `<g>` elements across custom interactive components into fully accessible keyboard-focusable elements by adding `tabIndex={0}`, `role=\"button\"`, `aria-pressed`, and `onKeyDown` listeners (supporting both `Enter` and `Space` activation keys). Affected components:\n   - `ArchitectureDiagram.tsx` (the main system blueprint inspector)\n   - `ControlCenterWorkspace.tsx` (the portal lattice topology map)\n   - `retailmesh/page.tsx`, `telecomverse/page.tsx`, and `oremesh/page.tsx` (all platform specific edge-node architecture maps)\n3. **SVG Keyboard Focus Indicators:** Custom focus indicators were added using SVG class hierarchies such as `group-focus-visible:stroke-white` on circles/rectangles, ensuring a beautiful and visible highlight for keyboard navigation on custom diagrams.\n4. **Header Keyboard Navigation Dropdowns:** Updated the main desktop navigation bar (`Header.tsx`) to implement the `group-focus-within` pattern. Submenu items (SOLUTIONS and ABOUT) are now fully accessible to keyboard users when tabbing, and all header links feature high-contrast premium `focus-visible` rings.\n5. **Command Center ARIA Optimization:** Updated `CommandCenter.tsx` to conform to WAI-ARIA combobox standards by adding `role=\"dialog\"`, `role=\"combobox\"`, `role=\"listbox\"`, `role=\"option\"`, `aria-autocomplete`, `aria-expanded`, and dynamic `aria-activedescendant` attributes pointing to the selected action list element.\n6. **Form Label & Input Field Accessibility:** Rewrote the global `ContactSection.tsx` form fields to associate `<label>` elements directly to `<input>` tags using corresponding `htmlFor` and `id` properties. Added custom, visible, theme-compliant focus indicators (`focus-visible:ring-[#009DFF]`) on every text input and the form submission button.\n7. **Animation Preferences Support:** Verified that standard premium page-reveals (`MotionReveal.tsx`) and dynamic ambient grid pools (`AnimatedBackgroundGrid.tsx`) fully respect the user's operating system settings via media query listeners for `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`, ensuring a calm, compliant experience for sensitive users.\n8. **Compliance & Verification:** Ran ESLint checks, verifying zero warnings or compilation errors. All changes are frontend-only, premium, mobile-responsive, and performant.","verified":true}}}
